OL,3,CAngela Rayner: No commitment to lift
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap by next election
OL,6,FITV News' Deputy Political Editor
OL,7,FAnushka Asthana grilled Angela Rayner
OL,8,Fand Rachel Reeves on their approach to
OL,9,Fchild poverty.
OL,11,FDeputy Labour Leader Angela Rayner has
OL,12,Frefused to commit to scrapping the two-
OL,13,Fchild limit on benefits, even if the
OL,14,Fparty win the General Election on July
OL,15,F4.
