OL,3,CAngela Rayner: No commitment to lift
OL,4,Ctwo-child benefit cap by next election
OL,6,FIn an exclusive interview with ITV
OL,7,FNews, Rayner avoided the question when
OL,8,Fasked directly and instead said:
OL,9,F"There's a lot of levers you can pull
OL,10,Fthat will help us alleviate child
OL,11,Fpoverty.
OL,13,F"The last Labour government took
OL,14,Fmillions of children out of poverty.
OL,15,FThe next Labour government will do the
OL,16,Fsame."
OL,18,FWhen asked if the policy would be gone
OL,19,Fwithin the next five years, she said:
OL,20,F"That's our plan, but we don't want to
OL,21,Fstart making commitments."
